From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 05:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] clk: qcom: nsscc-ipq5332: use BRANCH_HALT_SKIP on
 uniphy_port[12]_{rx,tx}_clk and port[12]_{rx,tx}_clk

The mainline clk framework's BRANCH_HALT halt-check polls CLK_OFF after
writing ENABLE, and times out with -EBUSY if CLK_OFF stays set within
20ms.  On IPQ5332 with a 10GBASE-R link to an external switch (Flint 3
/ RTL8372N), the recovered RX clock from the PCS only starts ticking
after the far-end SerDes actually transmits a valid 10GR signal — which
in turn requires the switch driver / external entity to bring the link
up.  So at the moment the kernel tries to enable the branch, CLK_OFF
genuinely IS set, and the framework gives up.

Vendor's qca-nss-dp / qca-ssdk stack writes the same CBCR ENABLE bit
without ever polling CLK_OFF, which is why their setup "works" — the
data path then comes up once the link is up, asynchronously to the
prepare/enable call.

Replace BRANCH_HALT with BRANCH_HALT_SKIP on the port1/port2 RCG sink
branches so mainline behaves the same way: write ENABLE, don't poll.
The kernel's other invariants (refcount tracking, parent enable
propagation) all still hold.

This is a runtime-only behavior change; the actual register layout and
semantics are unchanged.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/clk/qcom/nsscc-ipq5332.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/qcom/nsscc-ipq5332.c
@@ -752,7 +752,7 @@

 static struct clk_branch nss_cc_port1_rx_clk = {
 	.halt_reg = 0x4fc,
-	.halt_check = BRANCH_HALT,
+	.halt_check = BRANCH_HALT_SKIP,
 	.clkr = {
 		.enable_reg = 0x4fc,
 		.enable_mask = BIT(0),
@@ -770,7 +770,7 @@

 static struct clk_branch nss_cc_port1_tx_clk = {
 	.halt_reg = 0x504,
-	.halt_check = BRANCH_HALT,
+	.halt_check = BRANCH_HALT_SKIP,
 	.clkr = {
 		.enable_reg = 0x504,
 		.enable_mask = BIT(0),
@@ -806,7 +806,7 @@

 static struct clk_branch nss_cc_port2_rx_clk = {
 	.halt_reg = 0x50c,
-	.halt_check = BRANCH_HALT,
+	.halt_check = BRANCH_HALT_SKIP,
 	.clkr = {
 		.enable_reg = 0x50c,
 		.enable_mask = BIT(0),
@@ -824,7 +824,7 @@

 static struct clk_branch nss_cc_port2_tx_clk = {
 	.halt_reg = 0x514,
-	.halt_check = BRANCH_HALT,
+	.halt_check = BRANCH_HALT_SKIP,
 	.clkr = {
 		.enable_reg = 0x514,
 		.enable_mask = BIT(0),
@@ -1004,7 +1004,7 @@

